snippet.textDisplay:
I think one of the reasons Show Yourself really is better and more meaningful than Let It Go (altho I absolutely LOVE both!!!) is the message. Let It Go is about making a path for yourself, about defying the expectations of you and going out your own way. But it can be a very lonely thing—Elsa literally sets out to live in complete isolation in Let It Go.

But Show Yourself is about acceptance. That even though you're different, there is still a place for you in the world. And, more importantly, the people that matter the most to you (in Elsa's case, her mom) are 100% on your team, helping you grow into who you're supposed to be and being with you through the process.

Yes, it's great to be free to be yourself (as in Let It Go), but it's ultimately better that you are accepted for who you really are (as in Show Yourself). Don't mind me, just crying in the corner now.
